# Aggregate function :
                count(),
                min(),
                max(),
                avg(),
                sum()

# Clause : 
                GROUPBY,
                OrderBy,
                Having,
                Where

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Aggregate Function and Clause:
	1.	If you have added  or used any aggregated function along with some other column it is must that
		you have to write GROUPBY that column other wise get wrong result
		ex.select year,count(*) from cardata group by year 
		
    2. OrderBy always comes in the end after groupby
	3. When we have groupby or orderby in that case Where Clause can only works with existing columns.
	  If want to perform some thing with the new aggregated function or aggregated columns 
	  insted of 'where'  we have to use 'Having' clause after groupby.
	4.Having Is just a child of group by
	
WHERE VS Having

      Where clause is use to filter the actual columns present in the tables whereas,the Having clause is 
      used to filter the aggregated columns i.e(count(*),min(),max()) present in the tale .
      Having clause can come only if we have used the groupby ,can not use having clause alone.



